  "forensic": {
    "category": "video",
    "riskLevel": "low",
    "suspiciousPatterns": []
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "Raw H.265/HEVC Annex B byte-stream. 2-byte NALU header: byte1=F(1b)+nal_unit_type(6b)+nuh_layer_id_hi(1b), byte2=nuh_layer_id_lo(5b)+nuh_temporal_id_plus1(3b). Typical stream start: VPS(32)+SPS(33)+PPS(34)+IDR(19/20). SPS: profile_tier_level → general_profile_idc (1=Main, 2=Main10, 3=MainStillPicture), general_level_idc/3=level (e.g., 51=L5.1=4K@30fps, 62=L6.2=8K@120fps). SPS also contains: chroma_format_idc(0=mono, 1=4:2:0, 2=4:2:2, 3=4:4:4), bit_depth_luma/chroma_minus8, pic_width/height_in_luma_samples. H.265 in MP4 uses hvcC box (length-prefix, not Annex B).",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify 0x00 0x00 0x00 0x01 at offset 0 — Annex B start code",
      "NALU type from bytes 4-5: (byte4 & 0x7E) >> 1. Type 32=VPS, 33=SPS, 34=PPS, 19=IDR",
      "If first NALU is VPS (type 32), this is H.265 (not H.264 which starts at 32 only in HEVC)",
      "SPS profile: byte after PPS header → general_profile_idc (1=Main, 2=Main10)",
      "Check byte 5 bits 2-0 for nuh_temporal_id_plus1 (must be >= 1)"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "FFmpeg (hevc parser)",
